# CMS-Core Cursor/AI Rules

## Project Identity
Zero-dependency Node.js CMS with Drupal-inspired architecture.
Version: 0.0.80 | 91 services | 352 CLI commands

## Critical Rules

### 1. ZERO DEPENDENCIES
Never add npm packages. Build everything from Node.js built-ins:
- `node:http`, `node:fs`, `node:path`, `node:crypto`, `node:url`

### 2. SERVICE PATTERN
```javascript
export const name = 'serviceName';
export function init(context) { /* state + CLI */ return state; }
export function register(context, state) { /* hooks + routes */ }
```

### 3. WHY COMMENTS
```javascript
// WHY: Drupal separates published from default_revision
// to allow pending drafts on live content
```

### 4. DRUPAL ALIGNMENT
Study patterns at: `/Users/Alchemy/Projects/experiments/drupal-cms/web/core/modules/`

## Quick Reference

```bash
# Start
node index.js

# Test
node index.js help
node index.js content:list --type=article

# Drupal research
cat /Users/Alchemy/Projects/experiments/drupal-cms/web/core/modules/{module}/{module}.info.yml
```

## Structure
- `core/` — 91 services (don't add lightly)
- `modules/` — Feature modules (add here)
- `config/` — JSON configuration
- `content/` — Flat-file storage
- `themes/` — Layouts + skins

## Context Files
- `CLAUDE.md` — Full project harness
- `HANDOFF-CURRENT.md` — Current state
- `.claude/agents/` — Agent personas
- `.claude/skills/` — Research skills

## Don't
- Add npm dependencies
- Use callbacks (use async/await)
- Skip WHY comments
- Modify core/ without understanding boot.js

## Do
- Read handoff docs first
- Study Drupal equivalent
- Test via CLI
- Update HANDOFF-CURRENT.md
